# What are the implications of the results of the Ukrainian referendums?

## Summary
The referendums held in four occupied regions of Ukraine have returned huge majorities in favor of joining the Russian Federation (1), but are widely viewed as a sham and a violation of international law (2). The preordained outcome has been strongly condemned by both the government of Ukraine and its allies in the West (3), and the European Union has indicated it is preparing a new package of sanctions against Russia (4). Ukrainian President Volodymr Zelenskyy has said that any annexation in the modern world is a crime, and that Russiaâ€™s attempts to annex Ukrainian territory will mean there is nothing to talk about with this President of Russia (5).

